VALUES
-- Trading Education (2)
('trader-psychology-emotion-control', 'Trader Psychology: Managing Emotions', 'How to cope with emotions in trading: fear, greed, FOMO, and tilt. Practical techniques for maintaining control.', '<h2>Understanding Trader Emotions</h2><p>Every trader faces the same psychological challenges regardless of experience level. Fear manifests as premature position closing or inability to pull the trigger on valid setups. Greed appears as overleveraging and refusing to take profits. Tilt, borrowed from poker terminology, describes the irrational decision-making that follows a series of unexpected losses or missed opportunities.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6781273/pexels-photo-6781273.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Trader Psychology" /><h2>Practical Control Techniques</h2><p>Pre-market routine: review your trading plan, identify key levels and potential setups, and set maximum loss limits before the session begins. During trading, use checklists for each trade entry to prevent impulsive decisions. After significant losses, implement a mandatory cooling-off period (minimum 30 minutes) before placing the next trade.</p><h2>Long-Term Psychological Development</h2><p>Treat trading as a probability game rather than a personal battle. Each individual trade outcome is meaningless; only the statistical edge over hundreds of trades matters. Journaling helps identify emotional patterns. Review your journal weekly to spot recurring psychological triggers and develop specific countermeasures for each one.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6781273/pexels-photo-6781273.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Trading Education', ARRAY['psychology', 'emotions', 'trader', 'fear', 'greed', 'tilt', 'discipline'], 7, 'Trader Psychology: Emotion Control', 'Managing emotions in trading. Fear, greed, FOMO, and practical control techniques.', true, now()),

('forex-trading-strategies-proven-methods', 'Forex Trading Strategies: Proven Methods', 'Overview of proven forex trading strategies: trend following, counter-trend, breakout, and swing trading approaches.', '<h2>Trend Following Strategies</h2><p>Trend following is the most reliable approach for intermediate traders. Use moving average crossovers (50/200 EMA) for direction, enter on pullbacks to dynamic support levels, and trail stops using ATR-based calculations. This method captures the middle portion of trends while avoiding the noise of tops and bottoms. Works best on H4 and daily timeframes.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801874/pexels-photo-6801874.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Forex Strategies" /><h2>Breakout and Range Strategies</h2><p>Breakout strategies capitalize on price escaping established ranges. Identify consolidation zones on higher timeframes, then trade the breakout with confirmation from volume and momentum indicators. Range-bound strategies profit from mean reversion between support and resistance, using oscillators like RSI to time entries near range extremes.</p><h2>Swing Trading Approach</h2><p>Swing trading holds positions for 2-10 days, capturing multi-day price moves. Combine weekly trend analysis with daily entry signals. Use Fibonacci retracements for entry zones and previous swing highs/lows for target levels. This style suits traders who cannot monitor markets continuously but want to actively manage positions beyond simple buy-and-hold.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801874/pexels-photo-6801874.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Trading Education', ARRAY['trading strategies', 'forex', 'trend', 'breakout', 'swing trading', 'RSI', 'MACD'], 9, 'Forex Trading Strategies: Proven Methods', 'Proven forex trading strategies. Trend following, breakout, and swing trading.', true, now()),

-- Affiliate Programs (3)
('affiliate-marketing-forex-guide', 'Affiliate Marketing in Forex: Effective Strategies', 'How to earn through affiliate marketing in forex: traffic channels, content strategy, and traffic monetization.', '<h2>Building a Forex Affiliate Business</h2><p>Forex affiliate marketing offers substantial earning potential through recurring revenue share models. Top affiliates earn $10,000-$100,000+ monthly by driving qualified trader registrations to partner brokers. Success requires a long-term content strategy, understanding of trader needs, and ability to build trust with an audience that makes high-value financial decisions.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801874/pexels-photo-6801874.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Affiliate Marketing" /><h2>Traffic Acquisition Channels</h2><p>SEO-driven content sites rank for "best forex broker" and related keywords, delivering high-intent organic traffic. YouTube reviews and tutorials build authority and trust. Social media groups and Telegram channels create engaged communities. Paid advertising on Google and social platforms provides scalable but margin-sensitive traffic that requires careful ROI tracking.</p><h2>Conversion Optimization</h2><p>High-converting affiliate sites provide genuine value: honest broker reviews comparing real trading conditions, educational content that builds reader trust, and transparent disclosure of affiliate relationships. Comparison tables with key metrics (spreads, regulation, minimum deposit) help visitors make informed decisions. Regular content updates maintain search rankings and reader engagement.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801874/pexels-photo-6801874.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Affiliate Programs', ARRAY['affiliate', 'marketing', 'forex', 'partner', 'SEO', 'conversion', 'traffic'], 8, 'Affiliate Marketing in Forex', 'Effective affiliate marketing strategies in forex. Traffic channels and conversion optimization.', true, now()),

('multi-level-partner-network-broker', 'Multi-Level Partner Network for Brokers', 'Building and managing a multi-level partner network: structure, motivation, quality control, and scaling strategies.', '<h2>Network Architecture</h2><p>A multi-level partner network extends beyond direct Introducing Brokers to include sub-IBs recruited by your primary partners. Typical structures support 2-3 levels of referrals, with commission rates decreasing at each level. Level 1 IBs earn 40-60% revenue share, Level 2 sub-IBs receive 10-20%, and the broker retains the remainder. Clear hierarchy prevents conflicts and ensures fair compensation.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6693655/pexels-photo-6693655.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Partner Network" /><h2>Partner Motivation and Retention</h2><p>Beyond competitive commissions, partners value timely payouts (weekly preferred), transparent real-time reporting dashboards, marketing materials in multiple languages, and dedicated partner managers. Gamification elements like tiered status levels with increasing benefits (higher commissions, exclusive events, priority support) encourage partners to grow their client base.</p><h2>Quality Control</h2><p>Monitor partner quality metrics: client deposit rates, chargeback ratios, compliance complaint frequency, and client lifetime value. Partners generating low-quality traffic with high churn should receive warnings and ultimately termination. Implement automated fraud detection to identify suspicious patterns like duplicate registrations, self-referrals, or incentivized registrations.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6693655/pexels-photo-6693655.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Affiliate Programs', ARRAY['multi-level network', 'sub-IB', 'partner program', 'scaling', 'motivation'], 7, 'Multi-Level Partner Network for Brokers', 'Building a multi-level partner network for brokers. Structure, motivation, and scaling.', true, now()),

('broker-partner-program-overview', 'Broker Partner Program: How It Works', 'Structure of partner programs in the forex industry: commission models, tools for partners, and IB network management.', '<h2>Commission Model Types</h2><p>Forex partner programs offer three primary commission structures: CPA (Cost Per Acquisition) pays a one-time fee of $200-$1,000 per funded account, providing immediate income. Revenue Share pays ongoing commissions of 20-60% on client trading activity, creating passive recurring income. Hybrid models combine an upfront CPA payment with a lower ongoing revenue share percentage.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6694543/pexels-photo-6694543.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Partner Program" /><h2>Partner Tools and Resources</h2><p>Effective partner programs provide comprehensive toolkits: customizable landing pages and banners, real-time tracking links with UTM parameter support, detailed analytics dashboards showing clicks, registrations, deposits, and commissions. Advanced programs offer API access for partners to integrate tracking into their own systems and white-label registration pages for seamless brand integration.</p><h2>Managing IB Relationships</h2><p>Assign dedicated partner managers to high-performing IBs. Conduct regular performance reviews and provide actionable recommendations. Organize partner events and conferences to build loyalty and share best practices. Address payment issues promptly, as delayed or disputed commissions are the primary reason partners switch to competing brokers.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6694543/pexels-photo-6694543.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Affiliate Programs', ARRAY['partner program', 'IB', 'commissions', 'Revenue Share', 'CPA', 'referral system'], 7, 'Forex Broker Partner Program Overview', 'How forex broker partner programs work. Commission models and tools for partners.', true, now()),

-- Regulation (1)
('brokerage-licensing-complete-guide', 'Brokerage Licensing: Comprehensive Guide', 'What licenses does a broker need? The process of obtaining them, costs, and requirements across different jurisdictions.', '<h2>Types of Broker Licenses</h2><p>Broker licenses vary by jurisdiction and service scope. Investment firm licenses (CySEC CIF, FCA) cover a broad range of financial services including forex, CFDs, and securities. Specific forex dealer licenses (NFA/CFTC in the US) carry the highest capital requirements. Payment institution licenses may be needed separately for handling client funds depending on the jurisdiction.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/5716001/pexels-photo-5716001.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Brokerage Licensing" /><h2>Application Process</h2><p>The licensing process typically spans 6-18 months depending on the jurisdiction. Key steps include company incorporation, capital deposit, office establishment, hiring key personnel (compliance officer, directors), preparing business plans and procedures manuals, and submitting the application. CySEC averages 6-9 months, FCA takes 12-18 months, while offshore regulators can process applications in 2-4 months.</p><h2>Costs and Ongoing Requirements</h2><p>Initial costs range from $30,000-$50,000 for offshore licenses to $500,000+ for tier-1 jurisdictions (including capital requirements, legal fees, and setup costs). Annual maintenance includes regulatory fees, audit costs, compliance reporting, and capital adequacy requirements. Budget for ongoing legal counsel to navigate evolving regulatory requirements and periodic supervisory reviews.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/5716001/pexels-photo-5716001.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Regulation', ARRAY['license', 'regulation', 'CySEC', 'FCA', 'jurisdiction'], 15, 'Brokerage Licensing: Complete Guide', 'Detailed guide to obtaining a broker license. Comparing jurisdictions, requirements, costs, and timelines.', true, now()),

-- Marketing (1)
('broker-marketing-client-acquisition', 'Marketing for Brokers: Client Acquisition Strategies', 'Proven client acquisition channels for brokers: SEO, contextual advertising, affiliates, and social media.', '<h2>Digital Acquisition Framework</h2><p>Successful broker marketing combines multiple channels working in synergy. SEO builds long-term organic authority through educational content and broker comparison pages. Google Ads captures high-intent search traffic for terms like "open trading account." Social media advertising on Facebook, Instagram, and LinkedIn targets demographics matching your ideal client profile.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3184338/pexels-photo-3184338.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Broker Marketing" /><h2>Content Marketing Engine</h2><p>Educational content serves as both an acquisition and retention tool. Market analysis reports, trading tutorials, economic calendars, and webinars attract potential clients through search engines and social sharing. Gated premium content (e-books, strategy guides) captures email addresses for nurturing campaigns. Regular publication signals authority and keeps your brand visible in a competitive market.</p><h2>Measuring and Optimizing</h2><p>Track the full client journey from first touch to active trading. Calculate cost per acquisition (CPA) and client lifetime value (LTV) by channel. Optimize budget allocation toward channels with the best LTV-to-CPA ratio. Implement attribution modeling to understand how multiple touchpoints contribute to conversions rather than crediting only the last click.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/3184338/pexels-photo-3184338.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Marketing', ARRAY['marketing', 'advertising', 'SEO', 'client acquisition', 'affiliates'], 13, 'Marketing for Brokers: Client Acquisition', 'Proven client acquisition channels for brokers. SEO, Google Ads, affiliates, and social media.', true, now()),

-- Strategies (4)
('algorithmic-trading-profitable-bot', 'Algorithmic Trading: Building a Profitable Bot', 'How to create a profitable trading bot: algorithms, automation strategies, backtesting, and optimization.', '<h2>From Idea to Algorithm</h2><p>Building a profitable trading bot starts with a clear trading hypothesis based on market inefficiency or behavioral patterns. Define specific entry and exit rules, position sizing logic, and risk management parameters. Avoid complexity: the most robust algorithms use 3-5 rules maximum. Overly complex systems with dozens of parameters inevitably overfit to historical data and fail in live trading.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6120214/pexels-photo-6120214.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Trading Bot" /><h2>Development and Testing</h2><p>Code the strategy in Python (for flexibility) or MQL (for MetaTrader integration). Test on at least 5 years of historical data split into in-sample (development) and out-of-sample (validation) periods. Walk-forward analysis simulates real deployment by repeatedly optimizing on rolling windows and testing on unseen data. Only strategies that perform consistently out-of-sample proceed to live testing.</p><h2>Live Deployment</h2><p>Start live trading with minimal position sizes for at least 3 months. Compare live results to backtest expectations using statistical tests. Monitor for performance degradation that may indicate changing market conditions. Implement kill switches that halt trading when drawdown exceeds predefined thresholds or when execution quality deteriorates significantly.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6120214/pexels-photo-6120214.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Strategies', ARRAY['bots', 'algorithms', 'automation', 'strategies', 'backtesting'], 8, 'Algorithmic Trading: Building a Profitable Bot', 'How to create a profitable trading bot. Algorithms, backtesting, and live deployment.', true, now()),

('fundamental-analysis-news-markets', 'Fundamental Analysis: How News Impacts Markets', 'Understanding how economic data, central bank decisions, and geopolitical events move currency and stock prices.', '<h2>Economic Indicators That Move Markets</h2><p>Key economic releases drive significant price movements: Non-Farm Payrolls (NFP) impacts USD pairs with 50-100 pip moves, interest rate decisions from major central banks (Fed, ECB, BOJ) reshape trend directions, GDP data confirms or challenges growth narratives, and inflation reports (CPI) influence monetary policy expectations that ripple across all asset classes.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Fundamental Analysis" /><h2>Central Bank Analysis</h2><p>Central banks are the most influential market participants. Learn to interpret monetary policy statements, press conference language, and meeting minutes for forward guidance clues. Markets react not to absolute data but to deviations from expectations. A strong jobs report during a hawkish policy cycle has different implications than the same data during an easing cycle.</p><h2>Trading the News</h2><p>Two approaches dominate news trading: pre-positioning based on consensus expectations and deviation trading that reacts to surprise outcomes. Pre-positioning carries higher risk if expectations are wrong but captures larger moves. Deviation trading is safer but requires fast execution and often faces wider spreads and slippage during volatile news releases.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Strategies', ARRAY['fundamental analysis', 'news', 'economics', 'indicators', 'NFP'], 8, 'Fundamental Analysis: News Impact on Markets', 'How economic data and central bank decisions move markets. Trading the news effectively.', true, now()),

('technical-analysis-basics-strategies', 'Technical Analysis for Beginners: Basics and Strategies', 'Complete introduction to technical analysis: chart types, trends, support/resistance, and key indicators for new traders.', '<h2>Chart Reading Fundamentals</h2><p>Technical analysis studies price action to identify trading opportunities. Start with three chart types: line charts for quick trend overview, bar charts for open/high/low/close data, and Japanese candlesticks for visual pattern recognition. Candlestick charts are the most popular due to their ability to display price action psychology through body size, wick length, and color patterns.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Technical Analysis" /><h2>Trends, Support, and Resistance</h2><p>Markets move in trends (upward, downward, sideways) with price bouncing between support (buying interest) and resistance (selling interest) levels. Identify trends using higher highs and higher lows (uptrend) or lower highs and lower lows (downtrend). Support and resistance levels strengthen with each successful test and become more significant on higher timeframes.</p><h2>Essential Indicators</h2><p>Begin with three indicators: Moving Averages for trend direction, RSI for overbought/oversold conditions, and MACD for momentum and trend changes. Avoid loading charts with too many indicators as they often provide conflicting signals. Master these three before exploring Bollinger Bands, Fibonacci retracements, and volume-based indicators.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Strategies', ARRAY['technical analysis', 'indicators', 'candles', 'strategies', 'education'], 8, 'Technical Analysis for Beginners', 'Complete introduction to technical analysis. Charts, trends, and key indicators.', true, now()),

('capital-management-trading-rules', 'Capital Management in Trading: The 1-2% Rule', 'How proper capital management protects your trading account: position sizing, the 2% rule, and risk-reward ratios.', '<h2>The Foundation of Trading Survival</h2><p>Capital management determines whether you survive long enough for your strategy to work. The 1-2% rule states that no single trade should risk more than 1-2% of your total account balance. With a $10,000 account and 2% risk, your maximum loss per trade is $200. This means 10 consecutive losing trades only cost 20% of your account, leaving plenty of capital to recover.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801648/pexels-photo-6801648.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Capital Management" /><h2>Position Sizing Calculation</h2><p>Calculate position size based on your risk amount and stop loss distance: Position Size = Risk Amount / (Stop Loss in Pips * Pip Value). If risking $200 with a 50-pip stop loss and $10/pip value on EUR/USD, your maximum position is 0.4 lots. This formula ensures consistent risk regardless of stop loss distance, preventing larger losses on wider stops.</p><h2>Risk-Reward Ratios</h2><p>Target a minimum 1:2 risk-reward ratio on every trade. Risking $200 to potentially make $400 means you only need to win 34% of trades to be profitable. Higher ratios like 1:3 allow even lower win rates. Combine proper position sizing with favorable risk-reward ratios to create a mathematically robust trading approach that withstands losing streaks.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6801648/pexels-photo-6801648.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Strategies', ARRAY['capital management', 'risk management', '2% rule', 'stop loss', 'position sizing'], 7, 'Capital Management: The 1-2% Rule', 'How the 1-2% rule protects your trading capital. Position sizing and risk-reward ratios.', true, now()),

-- Technology (2)
('crm-for-broker-automation', 'CRM for Brokers: Client Operations Automation', 'How CRM helps automate broker client operations: marketing, sales, and support workflow optimization.', '<h2>Marketing Automation</h2><p>A broker CRM automates the entire marketing funnel: capturing leads from multiple channels (website forms, social media, partner referrals), scoring and segmenting them based on demographics and behavior, triggering personalized email and SMS sequences, and tracking campaign performance across channels. This replaces manual lead assignment and follow-up with systematic, data-driven processes.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/7567434/pexels-photo-7567434.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="CRM Automation" /><h2>Sales Process Optimization</h2><p>CRM automates sales workflows: new lead notifications with context, follow-up reminders, escalation rules for uncontacted leads, and pipeline visualization showing conversion bottlenecks. Sales managers gain visibility into team performance, call volumes, and conversion rates. Automated reporting eliminates manual data collection and provides real-time insights for decision-making.</p><h2>Support Integration</h2><p>Integrated support modules connect client inquiries across channels (email, chat, phone) with complete account context: trading history, deposit status, verification progress, and previous interactions. Automated routing directs inquiries to appropriate departments. Knowledge bases and chatbots handle common questions, freeing human agents for complex issues.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/7567434/pexels-photo-7567434.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Technology', ARRAY['CRM', 'automation', 'marketing', 'sales', 'clients'], 7, 'CRM for Brokers: Operations Automation', 'How CRM automates broker operations. Marketing, sales, and support optimization.', true, now()),

('choosing-trading-platform-for-broker', 'How to Choose a Trading Platform for Your Brokerage', 'Complete guide to selecting a trading platform: MT4, MT5, proprietary solutions, and key selection criteria.', '<h2>Platform Options Overview</h2><p>MetaTrader 4 remains the most popular retail forex platform with its vast ecosystem of indicators and Expert Advisors. MetaTrader 5 adds multi-asset support, depth of market, and improved backtesting. Proprietary platforms like cTrader and DXtrade offer modern interfaces and greater customization. White-label platforms provide full branding control but require more development investment.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Trading Platform" /><h2>Selection Criteria</h2><p>Evaluate platforms on: instrument coverage (forex, CFDs, crypto, equities), execution models supported (ECN, STP, Market Maker), customization and branding capabilities, mobile app quality, API access for third-party integrations, and total cost of ownership including licensing, hosting, and maintenance fees.</p><h2>Future-Proofing Your Choice</h2><p>Consider the platform''s development trajectory. Is the provider investing in mobile, web trading, and social features? Does the API support modern integration patterns? Can the platform scale as your client base grows? Switching platforms later is expensive and disruptive, so choosing a future-proof solution from the start saves significant long-term costs.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6770610/pexels-photo-6770610.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'Technology', ARRAY['platform', 'MT4', 'MT5', 'white-label', 'selection'], 8, 'Choosing a Trading Platform for Brokers', 'Guide to selecting a trading platform. MT4, MT5, proprietary, and key criteria.', true, now()),

-- General (1)
('trading-bots-advantages-2024', 'Advantages of Trading Bots in 2024', 'Why automated trading systems are becoming the standard: speed, consistency, emotional discipline, and 24/7 operation.', '<h2>Speed and Consistency</h2><p>Trading bots execute orders in milliseconds, capturing opportunities that human traders simply cannot react to fast enough. More importantly, bots execute every qualifying setup with identical precision whether it''s the first trade of the day or the hundredth. This consistency eliminates the performance degradation that humans experience from fatigue, distraction, and emotional interference.</p><img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/6120214/pexels-photo-6120214.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800" alt="Trading Bots" /><h2>Emotion-Free Trading</h2><p>Bots follow programmed rules without fear, greed, or hesitation. They never skip a trade because the last three were losers. They never increase position size after a winning streak. They never hold a losing position hoping for a reversal. This mechanical discipline is what most human traders aspire to but consistently fail to achieve under live market pressure.</p><h2>Multi-Market Coverage</h2><p>A single trader can only monitor a few instruments simultaneously. Trading bots scan hundreds of instruments across multiple timeframes and markets 24/7. This broad coverage ensures no opportunity is missed due to sleep, timezone differences, or attention limitations. Portfolio diversification through multi-bot strategies reduces correlation risk and smooths equity curves.</p>', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/6120214/pexels-photo-6120214.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800', 'en', true, 'MakeTrades Team', 'general', ARRAY['trading bots', 'automation', 'algorithmic trading', 'advantages', '2024'], 7, 'Advantages of Trading Bots in 2024', 'Why trading bots are becoming standard. Speed, consistency, and 24/7 operation.', true, now());